{"title_page": "Cristian Favela", "text_new": "{{short description|Mexican boxer}}\n{{BLP sources|date=October 2014}}\n{{Infobox boxer\n|name        = Cristian Favela\n|image       = \n|image_size  = \n|realname    = \n|nickname    = Filoso\n|weight      = [[Light Welterweight]]\n|height      = 5 ft 7 in (170 cm)\n|reach       = 69 in (175 cm)\n|nationality = Mexican\n|birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|1979|11|12}}\n|birth_place = [[Los Mochis]], [[Sinaloa]], [[Mexico]]\n|death_date  = \n|death_place = \n|style       = Orthodox\n|total       = 75\n|wins        = 38\n|losses      = 32\n|draws       = 5\n|no contests = \n|KO          = 24\n|medaltemplates =\n|show-medals =\n}}\n'''Cristian Favela''' (born November 12, 1979 in [[Los Mochis, Sinaloa]]) is a [[Mexican people|Mexican]] professional [[Boxing|boxer]] in the [[Welterweight]] division and is the former [[World Boxing Council|WBC Continental Americas]] [[Featherweight]] Champion.<ref>http://fightnights.com/boxers.php?id=1046</ref>\n\n==Pro career==\nOn October 15, 2010 Favela knocked out the veteran Alfredo Valenzuela at the Hotel Imperial in [[Agua Prieta, Sonora]], [[Mexico]].<ref>http://boxrec.com/show_display.php?show_id=609298</ref>\n\n===Professional Record===\n{{s-start}}\n|- style=\"margin:0.5em auto; font-size:95%;\"\n|align=\"center\" colspan=8|'''38 Wins''' (24 knockouts, 14 decisions), '''32 Losses''' (2 knockouts, 30 decisions)''', '''5 Draws'''\n|- style=\"margin:0.5em auto; font-size:95%;\"\n|align=center style=\"border-style: none none solid solid; background: #e3e3e3\"|'''Res.'''\n|align=center style=\"border-style: none none solid solid; background: #e3e3e3\"|'''Record'''\n|align=center style=\"border-style: none none solid solid; background: #e3e3e3\"|'''Opponent'''\n|align=center style=\"border-style: none none solid solid; background: #e3e3e3\"|'''Type'''\n|align=center style=\"border-style: none none solid solid; background: #e3e3e3\"|'''Rd., Time'''\n|align=center style=\"border-style: 