s==\n*{{boxrec|id=98407}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Favela, Cristian}}\n[[Category:Mexican male boxers]]\n[[Category:Boxers from Sinaloa]]\n[[Category:Welterweight boxers]]\n[[Category:1979 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "name_user": "TheAwesomeHwyh", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguated:Agua Caliente Casino\u2192Agua Caliente Casino Resort Spa", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cristian_Favela"}
{"title_page": "Only the Ring Finger Knows", "text_new": "{{Infobox animanga/Header\n| image           = Only the Ring Finger Knows.jpg\n| caption         = Cover of the first novel - ''Only the Ring Finger Knows: The Lonely Finger''\n| ja_kanji        = \u305d\u306e\u6307\u3060\u3051\u304c\u77e5\u3063\u3066\u3044\u308b\n| ja_romaji       = Sono Yubi Dake ga Shitte Iru\n| genre           = [[School story]], ''[[sh\u014dnen-ai]]''\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = light novel\n| author          = [[Satoru Kannagi]]\n| publisher       = \n| publisher_en    = {{English manga publisher | NA= [[Digital Manga Publishing]]}}\n| demographic     = Female\n| magazine        = \n| first           = November 2002\n| last            = September 25, 2008\n| volumes         = 5\n| volume_list     = \n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = manga\n| author          = [[Satoru Kannagi]]\n| illustrator     = [[Odagiri Hotaru]]\n| publisher       = [[Tokuma Shoten]]\n| publisher_en    = {{English manga publisher | NA= [[Digital Manga Publishing]]}}\n| demographic     = \n| magazine        = \n| published = 2002\n| volumes = 1\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Footer}}\n{{Nihongo|'''''Only the Ring Finger Knows'''''|\u305d\u306e\u6307\u3060\u3051\u304c\u77e5\u3063\u3066\u3044\u308b|Sono Yubi Dake ga Shitte Iru|lead=yes}} is the title of a [[sh\u014dnen-ai]] light novel series written by [[Satoru Kannagi]].  It was made into a manga illustrated by [[Hotaru Odagiri]], which has been licensed in the [[United States]] by [[Digital Manga Publishing]].\n\n==Plot==\nIn the school that Wataru Fujii goes to, when one wears matching rings on their right middle finger it is a sign of friendship, a ring on the right ring finger means single, and to wear matching rings on the left ring finger means a couple. One day Wataru accidentally switches rings with the very kind, handsome, popular senior, Yuichi Kazuki, because for some strange twist, their rings match. For reasons that Wataru doesn't understand, Yuichi becomes uncharacteristically mean to Wataru. After this strange incident, Wataru and Kazuki happened to meet more often, starting an electric relationship around the matching rings. Wataru starts to wonder why Yuichi's mood towards him switches to sweet-teasing to evil: is it because he just can't stand him or is it because he actually loves him?\n\nThis meeting of two students that everything seems to oppose, will led to the birth of an unexpected secret that only the ring finger knows.\n\n==Characters==\n===In Manga and Novel===\n;Wataru Fujii: The typical impulsive, brash high school student, with normal teenage problems. His life is turned upside down, however, after a fateful encounter with senior, Yuichi Kazuki who he finds wears a ring identical to his.\n\n;Yuichi Kazuki: A popular upperclassman, with a reputation of being a gentleman. He always gives a girl a proper let down. Generally seen as a kind person, his cutting remarks bewilder Wataru, whom he treats with contempt.\n\n;Karin Fujii: Wataru's younger sister. They look so much alike that people often mistake them as twins. She goes to an all-girls school and through strange circumstances, people think she and Yuichi have a relationship.\n\n;Kawamura: Wataru's classmate and class friend.  He has a crush on Mai Tachibana, the hottest girl in their class and is slightly resentful of Yuichi for \"stealing\" her away.\n\n;Touko: Yuichi's older cousin. Toko runs a jewelry shop, Parfait, and was the person who made Yuichi's ring. She enjoys going places with Yuichi to \"show him off\".\n\n;Mai Tachibana: The hottest girl in the class. She has a big crush on Yuichi and rejected Kawamura because of it.\n\n;Takako Kazuki: Yuichi's little niece who comes to visit him on his birthday. She has a dog. She gets \"engaged\" to Wataru accidentally.\n\n===Only In Novel===\n;Miho Ookusa: Pretty, popular first-year student who finds Wataru's ring and seems to show an interest in him. She is used to having guys notice her good looks and attempts to use her charm on Wataru, however he remains unaffected. To get his ring back, she tells Wataru that he must become friends with her, so they spend a large amount of time together and rumors about the two spread. It is later revealed that she stole Wataru's ring in the first place to cause him trouble because she had secretly been in love with Kazuki and had found out about their relationship. Kazuki later says, however, that although she might have once loved him she now liked Wataru.\n\n;Masanobu Asaka: He is Kazuki's rival and senior in college. He is very similar to Kazuki, in that both stand out for their looks and have similar mannerisms. Kazuki becomes jealous whenever he sees Asaka talking to Wataru and does not like Asaka. Wataru is oblivious to Asaka's feelings. Later on in the novel he falls deeply in love with Wataru resulting in making passes at Wataru when Yuichi isn't around. He has a brother who literally worships him. He also used to have a girlfriend by the name of Yuina but she died in a car accident. It mentions in the novel that Masnobu was deeply in love with but in the end they broke up. His broken ended up being broken by Wataru in the 4th novel of the series when he forcefully kissed Wataru which ends with Wataru saying that could not see each other anymore. In the end he ends up going to New York.\n\n;Shohei: Kazuki's older brother who doesn't approve of Wataru and Kazuki's relationship.\n\n==Media==\n''Only the Ring Finger Knows'' first began as a series of novels, and was later adapted into a manga.\n\n===Novels===\nIn conjunction with Digital Manga Publishing, five paperback novels are planned to be released based on the series:\n#''Only the Ring Finger Knows: The Lonely Ring Finger'': Released March 2006\n#''Only the Ring Finger Knows: The Left Hand Dreams of Him'': Released July 2006\n#''Only the Ring Finger Knows: The Ring Finger Falls Silent'': Released October 2006\n#''Only the Ring Finger Knows: The Ring Will Confess His Love'': Released June 10, 2009\n#''Only the Ring Finger Knows: The Finger Never Sleeps'': Released August 29, 2012\nThe Japanese version of volume 5 was published on September 27, 2008, which is the final volume. \nThe English version was released on August 29, 2012. <ref>http://www.junemanga.com/books/911/</ref>\n\n===Manga===\nThe manga version written by [[Satoru Kannagi]] and illustrated by [[Hotaru Odagiri]] only contains one volume and was published by [[Tokuma Shoten]] in Japan. The manga is now licensed by [[Digital Manga Publishing]].\n\n===Drama CD===\n''Only the Ring Finger Knows'' also has 4 volumes of [[Drama CD]]s to date, the first 3 based on the first part of each of the three novels, while the fourth drama is based on the second half of the third novel.\n\nCast:\n*[[Suzumura Kenichi]] as Fujii Wataru\n*[[Sakurai Takahiro]] as Kazuki Yuichi\n*[[Kamiya Hiroshi]] as Asaka Masanobu\n*[[Konishi Katsuyuki]] as Kazuki Shohei\n\n==Reception==\n{{Expand section|date=September 2008}}\nAs of mid-2005, the English-language edition of the manga was in its third printing, with sales of over 12,000 copies.<ref>http://www.publishersweekly.com/article/CA508674.html?</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.dmpbooks.com/titles?n=8 DMP official site for the manga]\n* {{ann|manga|3924}}\n* [http://www.publishersweekly.com/article/CA6470413.html Kannagi knows the Ring Finger]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Only The Ring Finger Knows}}\n[[Category:2002 Japanese novels]]\n[[Category:2002 manga]]\n[[Category:Digital Manga Publishing titles]]\n[[Category:Light novels]]\n[[Category:Sh\u014dnen-ai anime and manga]]\n[[Category:Tokuma Shoten manga]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox animanga/Header\n| image           = Only the Ring Finger Knows.jpg\n| caption         = Cover of the first novel - ''Only the Ring Finger Knows: The Lonely Finger''\n| ja_kanji        = \u305d\u306e\u6307\u3060\u3051\u304c\u77e5\u3063\u3066\u3044\u308b\n| ja_romaji       = Sono Yubi Dake ga Shitte Iru\n| genre           = [[School story]], ''[[sh\u014dnen-ai]]''\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = light novel\n| author          = [[Satoru Kannagi]]\n| publisher       = \n| publisher_en    = {{English manga publisher | NA= [[Digital Manga Publishing]]}}\n| demographic     = Female\n| magazine        = \n| first           = November 2002\n| last            = September 25, 2008\n| volumes         = 5\n| volume_list     = \n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = manga\n| author          = [[Satoru Kannagi]]\n| illustrator     = [[Odagiri Hotaru]]\n| publisher       = [[Tokuma Shoten]]\n| publisher_en    = {{English manga publisher | NA= [[Digital Manga Publishing]]}}\n| demographic     = \n| magazine        = \n| published = 2002\n| volumes = 1\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Footer}}\n{{Nihongo|'''''Only the Ring Finger Knows'''''|\u305d\u306e\u6307\u3060\u3051\u304c\u77e5\u3063\u3066\u3044\u308b|Sono Yubi Dake ga Shitte Iru|lead=yes}} is the title of a [[sh\u014dnen-ai]] light novel series written by [[Satoru Kannagi]].  It was made into a manga illustrated by [[Hotaru Odagiri]], which has been licensed in the [[United States]] by [[Digital Manga Publishing]].\n\n==Plot==\nIn the school that Wataru Fujii goes to, when one wears matching rings on their right middle finger it is a sign of friendship, a ring on the right ring finger means single, and to wear matching rings on the left ring finger means a couple. One day Wataru accidentally switches rings with the very kind, handsome, popular senior, Yuichi Kazuki, because for some strange twist, their rings match. For reasons that Wataru doesn't understand, Yuichi becomes uncharacteristically mean to Wataru. After this strange incident, Wataru and Kazuki happened to meet more often, starting an electric relationship around the matching rings. Wataru starts to wonder why Yuichi\u2019s mood towards him switches to sweet-teasing to evil: is it because he just can't stand him or is it because he actually loves him?\n\nThis meeting of two students that everything seems to oppose, will led to the birth of an unexpected secret that only the ring finger knows.\n\n==Characters==\n===In Manga and Novel===\n;Wataru Fujii: The typical impulsive, brash high school student, with normal teenage problems. His life is turned upside down, however, after a fateful encounter with senior, Yuichi Kazuki who he finds wears a ring identical to his.\n\n;Yuichi Kazuki: A popular upperclassman, with a reputation of being a gentleman. He always gives a girl a proper let down. Generally seen as a kind person, his cutting remarks bewilder Wataru, whom he treats with contempt.\n\n;Karin Fujii: Wataru's younger sister. They look so much alike that people often mistake them as twins. She goes to an all-girls school and through strange circumstances, people think she and Yuichi have a relationship.\n\n;Kawamura: Wataru's classmate and class friend.  He has a crush on Mai Tachibana, the hottest girl in their class and is slightly resentful of Yuichi for \"stealing\" her away.\n\n;Touko: Yuichi's older cousin. Toko runs a jewelry shop, Parfait, and was the person who made Yuichi's ring. She enjoys going places with Yuichi to \"show him off\".\n\n;Mai Tachibana: The hottest girl in the class. She has a big crush on Yuichi and rejected Kawamura because of it.\n\n;Takako Kazuki: Yuichi's little niece who comes to visit him on his birthday. She has a dog. She gets \"engaged\" to Wataru accidentally.\n\n===Only In Novel===\n;Miho Ookusa: Pretty, popular first-year student who finds Wataru's ring and seems to show an interest in him. She is used to having guys notice her good looks and attempts to use her charm on Wataru, however he remains unaffected. To get his ring back, she tells Wataru that he must become friends with her, so they spend a large amount of time together and rumors about the two spread. It is later revealed that she stole Wataru's ring in the first place to cause him trouble because she had secretly been in love with Kazuki and had found out about their relationship. Kazuki later says, however, that although she might have once loved him she now liked Wataru.\n\n;Masanobu Asaka: He is Kazuki's rival and senior in college. He is very similar to Kazuki, in that both stand out for their looks and have similar mannerisms. Kazuki becomes jealous whenever he sees Asaka talking to Wataru and does not like Asaka. Wataru is oblivious to Asaka's feelings. Later on in the novel he falls deeply in love with Wataru resulting in making passes at Wataru when Yuichi isn't around. He has a brother who literally worships him. He also used to have a girlfriend by the name of Yuina but she died in a car accident. It mentions in the novel that Masnobu was deeply in love with but in the end they broke up. His broken ended up being broken by Wataru in the 4th novel of the series when he forcefully kissed Wataru which ends with Wataru saying that could not see each other anymore. In the end he ends up going to New York.\n\n;Shohei: Kazuki's older brother who doesn't approve of Wataru and Kazuki's relationship.\n\n==Media==\n''Only the Ring Finger Knows'' first began as a series of novels, and was later adapted into a manga.\n\n===Novels===\nIn conjunction with Digital Manga Publishing, five paperback novels are planned to be released based on the series:\n#''Only the Ring Finger Knows: The Lonely Ring Finger'': Released March 2006\n#''Only the Ring Finger Knows: The Left Hand Dreams of Him'': Released July 2006\n#''Only the Ring Finger Knows: The Ring Finger Falls Silent'': Released October 2006\n#''Only the Ring Finger Knows: The Ring Will Confess His Love'': Released June 10, 2009\n#''Only the Ring Finger Knows: The Finger Never Sleeps'': Released August 29, 2012\nThe Japanese version of volume 5 was published on September 27, 2008, which is the final volume. \nThe English version was released on August 29, 2012. <ref>http://www.junemanga.com/books/911/</ref>\n\n===Manga===\nThe manga version written by [[Satoru Kannagi]] and illustrated by [[Hotaru Odagiri]] only contains one volume and was published by [[Tokuma Shoten]] in Japan. The manga is now licensed by [[Digital Manga Publishing]].\n\n===Drama CD===\n''Only the Ring Finger Knows'' also has 4 volumes of [[Drama CD]]s to date, the first 3 based on the first part of each of the three novels, while the fourth drama is based on the second half of the third novel.\n\nCast:\n*[[Suzumura Kenichi]] as Fujii Wataru\n*[[Sakurai Takahiro]] as Kazuki Yuichi\n*[[Kamiya Hiroshi]] as Asaka Masanobu\n*[[Konishi Katsuyuki]] as Kazuki Shohei\n\n==Reception==\n{{Expand section|date=September 2008}}\nAs of mid-2005, the English-language edition of the manga was in its third printing, with sales of over 12,000 copies.<ref>http://www.publishersweekly.com/article/CA508674.html?</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.dmpbooks.com/titles?n=8 DMP official site for the manga]\n* {{ann|manga|3924}}\n* [http://www.publishersweekly.com/article/CA6470413.html Kannagi knows the Ring Finger]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Only The Ring Finger Knows}}\n[[Category:2002 Japanese novels]]\n[[Category:2002 manga]]\n[[Category:Digital Manga Publishing titles]]\n[[Category:Light novels]]\n[[Category:Sh\u014dnen-ai anime and manga]]\n[[Category:Tokuma Shoten manga]]\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200ePlot:Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: \u2019s \u2192 's", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Only_the_Ring_Finger_Knows"}
{"title_page": "Jaungulbene Manor", "text_new": "{{refimprove|date=April 2020}}\n{{short description|Manor house in Latvia}}\n{{Infobox building\n|image=Jaungulbenes pils 2000-04-21.jpg\n|caption=\n|name=Jaungulbene Manor\n|location_town=[[Gulbene municipality]]\n|location_country=[[Latvia]]\n|latitude=\n|longitude=\n|architect=\n|client= Otto Wilhelm Leopold von Transehe\n|engineer=\n|construction_start_date= \n|completion_date= [[1878]]\n|date_demolished=\n|cost=\n|structural_system=\n|style=Tudor [[Neo-Gothic]]\n}}\n\n'''Jaungulbene Manor''' ({{lang-lv|Jaungulbenes mui\u017eas pils}}; {{lang-de|Schloss Neu-Schwanenburg}}) is a manor house in the historical region of [[Vidzeme]], in northern [[Latvia]]. It was built in [[Neo-Gothic|Tudor neo-Gothic style]] and completed in 1878. From 1927 until the 1990s the building housed an agricultural school.<ref>(Zar\u0101ns, Albert)</ref>\n\n<gallery>\nJaungulbene Manor, 2013, 1.jpg\nJaungulbene m\u00f5is 01.JPG\nJaungulbene m\u00f5is 13.JPG\nJaungulbene m\u00f5is 19.JPG\nJaungulbene m\u00f5is 17.JPG\n</gallery>\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of palaces and manor houses in Latvia]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n*{{cite book\n| last = Zar\u0101ns\n| first = Alberts\n| authorlink = Alberts Zar\u0101ns\n| title =Latvijas pilis un mui\u017eas. Castles and manors of Latvia.\n| language = Latvian, English\n| publisher =\n| location = Riga\n| series =\n| year = 2006\n| isbn = 9984-785-05-X\n| oclc = 72358861\n}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{in lang|lv}} [https://web.archive.org/web/20131016060225/http://www.pilis.lv/a_pnm/view.php?id=76&prop_id=211 Jaungulbene Manor]\n* {{Commons category-inline}}\n\n{{Castles in Latvia}}\n\n{{coord|57.0605|N|26.5963|E|source:wikidata|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Manor houses in Latvia]]\n\n\n{{Latvia-castle-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{refimprove|date=April 2020}}\n{{short description|Manor house in Latvia}}\n{{Infobox building\n|image=Jaungulbenes pils 2000-04-21.jpg\n|caption=\n|name=Jaungulbene Manor\n|location_town=[[Gulbene municipality]]\n|location_country=[[Latvia]]\n|latitude=\n|longitude=\n|architect=\n|client= Otto Wilhelm Leopold von Transehe\n|engineer=\n|construction_start_date= \n|completion_date= 1878\n|date_demolished=\n|cost=\n|structural_system=\n|style=Tudor [[Neo-Gothic]]\n}}\n\n'''Jaungulbene Manor''' ({{lang-lv|Jaungulbenes mui\u017eas pils}}; {{lang-de|Schloss Neu-Schwanenburg}}) is a manor house in the historical region of [[Vidzeme]], in northern [[Latvia]]. It was built in Tudor neo-Gothic style and completed in 1878. From 1927 until the 1990s the building housed an agricultural school.<ref>(Zar\u0101ns, Albert)</ref>\n\n<gallery>\nJaungulbene Manor, 2013, 1.jpg\nJaungulbene m\u00f5is 01.JPG\nJaungulbene m\u00f5is 13.JPG\nJaungulbene m\u00f5is 19.JPG\nJaungulbene m\u00f5is 17.JPG\n</gallery>\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of palaces and manor houses in Latvia]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n*{{cite book\n| last = Zar\u0101ns\n| first = Alberts\n| authorlink = Alberts Zar\u0101ns\n| title =Latvijas pilis un mui\u017eas. Castles and manors of Latvia.\n| language = Latvian, English\n| publisher =\n| location = Riga\n| series =\n| year = 2006\n| isbn = 9984-785-05-X\n| oclc = 72358861\n}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{in lang|lv}} [https://web.archive.org/web/20131016060225/http://www.pilis.lv/a_pnm/view.php?id=76&prop_id=211 Jaungulbene Manor]\n* {{Commons category-inline}}\n\n{{Castles in Latvia}}\n\n{{coord|57.0605|N|26.5963|E|source:wikidata|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Manor houses in Latvia]]\n\n\n{{Latvia-castle-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Stickymatch", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jaungulbene_Manor"}
{"title_page": "Daniel A. D'Aniello", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name        = Daniel A. D'Aniello\n| image       =\n| caption     =\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1946|9|14}}\n| birth_place = [[Butler, Pennsylvania]], US\n| death_date  =\n| death_place =\n| occupation  = Chairman, [[The Carlyle Group]]\n| alma_mater  = [[Syracuse University]]<br/>[[Harvard Business School]]\n| spouse      = Gayle D'Aniello\n| children    = 2 daughters\n| salary      =\n| networth    = US$2.9 billion (January 2018)<ref name=Forbes>{{cite web|title=Daniel D'Aniello|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/daniel-daniello/|website=Forbes.com|accessdate=15 January 2018}}</ref>\n| website     = \n}}\n\n'''Daniel Anthony D'Aniello''' (born September 14, 1946) is an American [[billionaire]] businessman.<ref name=\"businessweek\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/tosv2.html?vid=&uuid=6701caa0-0ba9-11e9-9981-07da29c48706&url=L3Jlc2VhcmNoL3N0b2Nrcy9wZW9wbGUvcGVyc29uLmFzcD9wZXJzb25JZD0xNzQ5OTAmdGlja2VyPUNH|title=Bloomberg - Are you a robot?|website=Bloomberg.com|accessdate=29 December 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"forbes2007\">{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/lists/2007/54/richlist07_Daniel-DAniello_Y81T.html|title=#165 Daniel D'Aniello - Forbes.com|website=Forbes.com|accessdate=29 December 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"carlyle\">{{cite web|url=https://www.carlyle.com/about-carlyle/team/daniel-daniello|title=Daniel A. D'Aniello - The Carlyle Group|website=Carlyle.com|accessdate=29 December 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"martin\">{{cite web|url=https://whitman.syr.edu/programs-and-academics/centers-and-institutes/falcone/for-students/daniellobio.aspx|title=Daniel A. D'Aniello '68 BS - Syracuse University Whitman School of Management|website=Whitman.syr.edu|accessdate=29 December 2018}}</ref> He is the cofounder and chairman of [[the Carlyle Group]], a [[private equity]] firm headquartered in [[Washington, D.C.]]<ref name=\"carlyle\"/>\n\n==Biography==\n===Early life===\nD'Aniello grew up in [[Butler, Pennsylvania]], and graduated from [[Butler Senior High School]].<ref name=\"forbes2007\"/> He graduated from [[Syracuse University]] [[magna cum laude]] in 1968, where he was a member of [[Beta Gamma Sigma]], an honor society for business students and scholars.<ref name=\"businessweek\"/><ref name=\"forbes2007\"/><ref name=\"martin\"/> He received an M.B.A. from the [[Harvard Business School]] in 1974, where he was a Teagle Foundation Fellow.<ref name=\"businessweek\"/><ref name=\"forbes2007\"/><ref name=\"martin\"/>\n\n===Career===\nHe served as a financial officer at [[Pepsico]] and [[TWA]].<ref name=\"businessweek\"/><ref name=\"forbes2007\"/><ref name=\"carlyle\"/><ref name=\"martin\"/> He later served as Vice President for Finance and Development at the [[Marriott Corp.|Marriott Corporation]].<ref name=\"businessweek\"/><ref name=\"forbes2007\"/><ref name=\"carlyle\"/><ref name=\"martin\"/> He was responsible for the valuation of major mergers, acquisitions, divestitures, debt and equity offerings, and [[project finance|project financings]].<ref name=\"carlyle\"/>\n\nIn 1987, he co-founded the Carlyle Group with [[William E. Conway Jr.]], and [[David Rubenstein]].<ref name=\"businessweek\"/><ref name=\"forbes2007\"/><ref name=\"carlyle\"/><ref name=\"martin\"/> He now serves as Chairman of the Board.<ref name=\"carlyle\"/>\n\nHe serves on the Board of Trustees of the [[American Enterprise Institute]].<ref name=\"businessweek\"/><ref name=\"aei\">{{cite web|url=http://www.aei.org/about/board-of-trustees/|title=Board of Trustees|date=16 April 2014|website=Aei.org|accessdate=29 December 2018}}</ref> He also serves on the Board of Trustees of his alma mater, [[Syracuse University]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://trustees.syr.edu/Public/SitePages/Trustees.aspx|title=Home - Trustees|website=Trustees.syr.edu|language=en-us|access-date=2017-04-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://dc.syr.edu/alumni/alumni-profiles/daniel-daniello-profile.html|title=Daniel D'Aniello {{!}} Syracuse University|last=Services|first=Web|website=Dc.syr.edu|access-date=2017-04-19}}</ref> and on the Corporate Advisory Council of its [[Martin J. Whitman School of Management]]<ref name=\"businessweek\" /><ref name=\"carlyle\" /> and the [[Institute for Veterans and Military Families|IVMF advisory board]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ivmf.syracuse.edu/team-member/daniel-a-daniello/|title=Daniel A. D'Aniello - IVMF|website=Ivmf.syracuse.edu|language=en-US|access-date=2017-04-19}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2017, D'Aniello was awarded the ''Arents Award'' which is Syracuse University's highest alumni honor.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news.syr.edu/2017/07/four-accomplished-alumni-to-receive-arents-awards-during-orange-central/|title=Four Accomplished Alumni to Receive Arents Awards During Orange Central|work=SU News|access-date=2017-07-29|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n===Philanthropy===\nDaniel and Gayle D'Aniello support the [[Washington National Opera]].<ref name=\"Washington National Opera\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.kennedy-center.org/events/?event=OPOSA |title=Archived copy |access-date=2014-11-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141112201815/http://www.kennedy-center.org/events/?event=OPOSA |archive-date=2014-11-12 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref>\n\n{{quote|text=\"I'm a good Italian boy,\" he said. \"l love opera and anything that ends in a vowel.\"|sign=Daniel D'Aniello|newspaper=[[The Washington Post]]|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/business/capitalbusiness/the-scene-week-of-sept-22/2014/09/21/a4ccd416-3dbc-11e4-b03f-de718edeb92f_story.html}}\n\n===Personal life===\nHe lives in [[Vienna, Virginia]] with his wife of thirty-nine years, Gayle.{{Citation needed|date=January 2020}} Together they have two daughters, Dana and Bethany.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://dc.syr.edu/alumni/alumni-profiles/daniel-daniello-profile.html|title=Daniel D\u2019Aniello - Syracuse University|website=Dc.syr.edu|accessdate=29 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Carlyle Group}}\n{{Private equity investors}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:D'Aniello, Daniel A.}}\n\n[[Category:1946 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:20th-century American businesspeople]]\n[[Category:21st-century American businesspeople]]\n[[Category:American billionaires]]\n[[Category:American chief executives of financial services companies]]\n[[Category:American chief financial officers]]\n[[Category:American Enterprise Institute]]\n[[Category:American financiers]]\n[[Category:American financial analysts]]\n[[Category:American investors]]\n[[Category:American money managers]]\n[[Category:Businesspeople from Pennsylvania]]\n[[Category:Carlyle Group people]]\n[[Category:Harvard Business School alumni]]\n[[Category:People from Butler County, Pennsylvania]]\n[[Category:PepsiCo people]]\n[[Category:Private equity and venture capital investors]]\n[[Category:Syracuse University alumni]]\n[[Category:Syracuse University trustees]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name        = Daniel A. D'Aniello\n| image       =\n| caption     =\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1946|9|14}}\n| birth_place = [[Butler, Pennsylvania]], US\n| death_date  =\n| death_place =\n| occupation  = Chairman, [[The Carlyle Group]]\n| alma_mater  = [[Syracuse University]]<br/>[[Harvard Business School]]\n| spouse      = Gayle D'Aniello\n| children    = 2 daughters\n| salary      =\n| networth    = US$2.9 billion (January 2018)<ref name=Forbes>{{cite web|title=Daniel D'Aniello|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/daniel-daniello/|website=Forbes.com|accessdate=15 January 2018}}</ref>\n| website     = \n}}\n\n'''Daniel Anthony D'Aniello''' (born September 14, 1946) is an American [[billionaire]] businessman.<ref name=\"businessweek\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/tosv2.html?vid=&uuid=6701caa0-0ba9-11e9-9981-07da29c48706&url=L3Jlc2VhcmNoL3N0b2Nrcy9wZW9wbGUvcGVyc29uLmFzcD9wZXJzb25JZD0xNzQ5OTAmdGlja2VyPUNH|title=Bloomberg - Are you a robot?|website=Bloomberg.com|accessdate=29 December 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"forbes2007\">{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/lists/2007/54/richlist07_Daniel-DAniello_Y81T.html|title=#165 Daniel D'Aniello - Forbes.com|website=Forbes.com|accessdate=29 December 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"carlyle\">{{cite web|url=https://www.carlyle.com/about-carlyle/team/daniel-daniello|title=Daniel A. D'Aniello - The Carlyle Group|website=Carlyle.com|accessdate=29 December 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"martin\">{{cite web|url=https://whitman.syr.edu/programs-and-academics/centers-and-institutes/falcone/for-students/daniellobio.aspx|title=Daniel A. D'Aniello '68 BS - Syracuse University Whitman School of Management|website=Whitman.syr.edu|accessdate=29 December 2018}}</ref> He is the cofounder and chairman of [[the Carlyle Group]], a [[private equity]] firm headquartered in [[Washington, D.C.]].<ref name=\"carlyle\"/>\n\n==Biography==\n===Early life===\nD'Aniello grew up in [[Butler, Pennsylvania]], and graduated from [[Butler Senior High School]].<ref name=\"forbes2007\"/> He graduated from [[Syracuse University]] [[magna cum laude]] in 1968, where he was a member of [[Beta Gamma Sigma]], an honor society for business students and scholars.<ref name=\"businessweek\"/><ref name=\"forbes2007\"/><ref name=\"martin\"/> He received an M.B.A. from the [[Harvard Business School]] in 1974, where he was a Teagle Foundation Fellow.<ref name=\"businessweek\"/><ref name=\"forbes2007\"/><ref name=\"martin\"/>\n\n===Career===\nHe served as a financial officer at [[Pepsico]] and [[TWA]].<ref name=\"businessweek\"/><ref name=\"forbes2007\"/><ref name=\"carlyle\"/><ref name=\"martin\"/> He later served as Vice President for Finance and Development at the [[Marriott Corp.|Marriott Corporation]].<ref name=\"businessweek\"/><ref name=\"forbes2007\"/><ref name=\"carlyle\"/><ref name=\"martin\"/> He was responsible for the valuation of major mergers, acquisitions, divestitures, debt and equity offerings, and [[project finance|project financings]].<ref name=\"carlyle\"/>\n\nIn 1987, he co-founded the Carlyle Group with [[William E. Conway Jr.]], and [[David Rubenstein]].<ref name=\"businessweek\"/><ref name=\"forbes2007\"/><ref name=\"carlyle\"/><ref name=\"martin\"/> He now serves as Chairman of the Board.<ref name=\"carlyle\"/>\n\nHe serves on the Board of Trustees of the [[American Enterprise Institute]].<ref name=\"businessweek\"/><ref name=\"aei\">{{cite web|url=http://www.aei.org/about/board-of-trustees/|title=Board of Trustees|date=16 April 2014|website=Aei.org|accessdate=29 December 2018}}</ref> He also serves on the Board of Trustees of his alma mater, [[Syracuse University]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://trustees.syr.edu/Public/SitePages/Trustees.aspx|title=Home - Trustees|website=Trustees.syr.edu|language=en-us|access-date=2017-04-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://dc.syr.edu/alumni/alumni-profiles/daniel-daniello-profile.html|title=Daniel D'Aniello {{!}} Syracuse University|last=Services|first=Web|website=Dc.syr.edu|access-date=2017-04-19}}</ref> and on the Corporate Advisory Council of its [[Martin J. Whitman School of Management]]<ref name=\"businessweek\" /><ref name=\"carlyle\" /> and the [[Institute for Veterans and Military Families|IVMF advisory board]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ivmf.syracuse.edu/team-member/daniel-a-daniello/|title=Daniel A. D'Aniello - IVMF|website=Ivmf.syracuse.edu|language=en-US|access-date=2017-04-19}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2017, D'Aniello was awarded the ''Arents Award'' which is Syracuse University's highest alumni honor.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news.syr.edu/2017/07/four-accomplished-alumni-to-receive-arents-awards-during-orange-central/|title=Four Accomplished Alumni to Receive Arents Awards During Orange Central|work=SU News|access-date=2017-07-29|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n===Philanthropy===\nDaniel and Gayle D'Aniello support the [[Washington National Opera]].<ref name=\"Washington National Opera\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.kennedy-center.org/events/?event=OPOSA |title=Archived copy |access-date=2014-11-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141112201815/http://www.kennedy-center.org/events/?event=OPOSA |archive-date=2014-11-12 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref>\n\n{{quote|text=\"I'm a good Italian boy,\" he said. \"l love opera and anything that ends in a vowel.\"|sign=Daniel D'Aniello|newspaper=[[The Washington Post]]|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/business/capitalbusiness/the-scene-week-of-sept-22/2014/09/21/a4ccd416-3dbc-11e4-b03f-de718edeb92f_story.html}}\n\n===Personal life===\nHe lives in [[Vienna, Virginia]] with his wife of thirty-nine years, Gayle.{{Citation needed|date=January 2020}} Together they have two daughters, Dana and Bethany.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://dc.syr.edu/alumni/alumni-profiles/daniel-daniello-profile.html|title=Daniel D\u2019Aniello - Syracuse University|website=Dc.syr.edu|accessdate=29 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Carlyle Group}}\n{{Private equity investors}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:D'Aniello, Daniel A.}}\n\n[[Category:1946 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:20th-century American businesspeople]]\n[[Category:21st-century American businesspeople]]\n[[Category:American billionaires]]\n[[Category:American chief executives of financial services companies]]\n[[Category:American chief financial officers]]\n[[Category:American Enterprise Institute]]\n[[Category:American financiers]]\n[[Category:American financial analysts]]\n[[Category:American investors]]\n[[Category:American money managers]]\n[[Category:Businesspeople from Pennsylvania]]\n[[Category:Carlyle Group people]]\n[[Category:Harvard Business School alumni]]\n[[Category:People from Butler County, Pennsylvania]]\n[[Category:PepsiCo people]]\n[[Category:Private equity and venture capital investors]]\n[[Category:Syracuse University alumni]]\n[[Category:Syracuse University trustees]]\n", "name_user": "Marquardtika", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Daniel_A._D%27Aniello"}
{"title_page": "K\u014dtetsu Sangokushi", "text_new": "{{More citations needed|date=March 2015}}\n\n{{Infobox animanga/Header\n| image           = Koutetsu Sangokushi.jpg\n| image_size      = 230px\n| caption         = Promotional poster for the anime ''K\u014dtetsu Sangokushi''\n| ja_kanji        = \u92fc\u9244\u4e09\u56fd\u5fd7\n| genre           = [[Action genre|Action]], [[Supernatural]], [[Historical]], [[Sh\u014dnen-ai]]\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Video\n| type            = tv series\n| director        = Satoshi Saga<br />[[Tetsuya Endo (director)|Tetsuya Endo]] <small>(Chief Director)</small>\n| producer        = Masanori Miyake\n| writer          = Natsuko Takahashi\n| music           = Yuji Toriyama\n| studio          = Picture Magic\n| network         = [[TV Tokyo]]\n| first           = April 5, 2007\n| last            = September 27, 2007\n| episodes        = 25\n| episode_list    = Koutetsu Sangokushi#Episodes\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Footer}}\n\n{{nihongo|'''''K\u014dtetsu Sangokushi'''''|\u92fc\u9244\u4e09\u56fd\u5fd7}} is a 2007 Japanese [[anime]] loosely based on the Chinese historical fiction novel ''[[Romance of the Three Kingdoms]]''. It was produced by [[Nihon Ad Systems|NAS]] and [[Konami|Konami Digital Entertainment]].\n\n==Plot==\nThe Imperial Seal has been passed down through the generations of guardians since ancient times. It confers great power unto those it chooses. This is the story of its guardians.\n\nIt is a time of war, when great armies clash in terrible battles and great heroes carve their names in history. It is also a time of death and destruction, when the people of the land live in constant fear of the sword. Onto this stage steps the reluctant Rikuson Hakugen ([[Lu Xun (Three Kingdoms)|Lu Xun]]), whose family had been the guardians of the Imperial Seal up until it was stolen by Hakufu Sonsaku, the ruler of the kingdom of Go. At the behest of his mentor, Koumei Shoukatsuryou, ([[Zhuge Liang]]) Rikuson offers his services to Sonsaku Sonken with the intention of confirming the will of the Imperial Seal. However, assassins strike down Sonsaku and the Imperial Seal is lost. So begins, Rikuson's journey to recover the Imperial Seal and discover, with the help of his friends, his destiny.\n\n==Characters==\n{{MOS|section|reason=Voice actors should be listed in western order|date=October 2015}}\n\nAnime name followed by (Romance of the Three Kingdoms name) followed by Japanese voice actor.\n\n*  Ekitoku Chouhi ([[Zhang Fei]]): [[Onosaka Masaya]]\n*  Chouryou Bun'en ([[Zhang Liao]]): [[Yamaguchi Kappei]]\n*  Choujou Kofu ([[Zhang Zhao]]): [[Miyazawa Tadashi]]\n*  Shiryuu Chou'un ([[Zhao Yun]]): [[Sugiyama Noriaki]]\n*  Kannei Kouha ([[Gan Ning]]): [[Suwabe Junichi]]\n*  Unchou Kan'u ([[Guan Yu]]): [[Ohkawa Tohru]]\n*  Kougai Koufuku ([[Huang Gai]]): [[Ohkawa Tohru]]\n*  Genyou Kouso ([[Huang Zu]]): [[Okiayu Ryotaro]]\n*  Kyocho Chuukou (Xu Zhu)\n*  Hakugen Rikuson ([[Lu Xun (Three Kingdoms)|Lu Xun]]): [[Miyano Mamoru]]\n*  Shikei Roshoku ([[Lu Su]]): [[Nojima Kenji]]\n*  Shimei Ryoumou ([[Lu Meng]]): [[Ishida Akira]]\n*  Ryousou Kouketsu ([[Ling Cao]]): [[Inoue Kazuhiko]]\n*  Ryoutou Kouseki ([[Ling Tong]]): [[Saiga Mitsuki]]\n*  Gentoku Ryuubi ([[Liu Bei]]): [[Satou Rina]]\n*  Shiyu Shokatsukin ([[Zhuge Jin]]): [[Yusa Kouji]]\n*  Koumei Shokatsuryou ([[Zhuge Liang]]): [[Koyasu Takehito]]\n*  Youhei Shuutai ([[Zhou Tai]])\n*  Koukin Shuuyu ([[Zhou Yu]]): [[Shin-ichiro Miki]]\n*  Chuubou Sonken ([[Sun Quan]]): [[Nabatame Hitomi]]\n*  Hakufu Sonsaku ([[Sun Ce]]): [[Matsumoto Yasunori]]\n*  Shikou Soujin ([[Cao Ren]]): [[Iwasaki Masami]]\n*  Moutoku Sousou ([[Cao Cao]]): [[Mitsuya Yuji]]\n*  Taishiji Shigi ([[Taishi Ci]]): [[Itou Kentarou]]\n\n==Release==\n\n{{empty section|date=March 2015}}\n\n==Episodes==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"  style=\"width:78%; background:#fff;\"\n|- style=\"border-bottom:3px solid #CCF\"\n! # !! Episode Name !! Original air date\n|-\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 1\n| T